{"vocabInfos":[{"lsjDefs":"<b> ἄπειμι</b>, <br /> (εἰμί <br /><Level1><b>__A</b></Level1> <b>sum</b>), <i>imperfect</i> ἀπῆν (later ἀπήμην[<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" “POxy.” 1204.23 (3rd c.AD))\">Refs 3rd c.AD+</a>], <i>2nd pers.</i><i>singular</i> ἀπῆσθα[<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Philoctetes” 379\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; <i>Epic dialect</i> ἀπέην[<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad” 20.7, _3rd.pers._ _plural_ ἄπεσαν [prev. work] 10.357\">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]: <i>future</i> ἀπέσομαι[<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Aristophanes Comicus “Nubes” 887\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; <i>Epic dialect</i> ἀπέσσομαι[<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Odyssea Homerus Epicus “Odyssey” 8.150, _3rd.pers._ _sing._ ἀπεσσεῖται [prev. work] 19.302\">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]:—<b>to be away</b> or <b>far from,</b> with <i>genitive</i>, ὁππότε πάτρης ἧς ἀπέῃσιν ἀνήρ [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\"[prev. work] 169, compare 20.155, +others; ἐὰν δ᾽ ἀπῇ τούτων τὸ χαίρειν 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Antigone” 1169; ἀ. ἀπὸ τῶν ἰδίων 5th c.BC: Thucydides Historicus 1.141: with _dative_, φίλοισιν 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Medea” 179 (Lyric poetry), compare “Tr.” 393, 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 4.1, 5th c.BC: Thucydides Historicus 2.61, etc.: but mostly, \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__A.2</b></Level3> <i>absolutely</i>, <b>to be away</b> or <b>absent,</b> and of things, <b>to be wanting,</b> οἵ τ᾽ ὄντες οἵ τ᾽ ἀπόντες, i.e. all that are, every one, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Antigone” 1109; τὰς οὔσας τέ μου καὶ τὰς ἀπούσας ἐλπίδας [prev. author] “El.” 306 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; of the dead, variant in [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Hecuba” 312\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; τοῦ θεοῦ ἀπεόντος the god <b>not being counted,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC